  "why": "AutoDAN explicitly formulates and optimizes for attacker-chosen target outputs (affirmative responses that begin with a predefined prefix such as “Sure, here is how to [Qi]”). The method defines a loss as the negative log-likelihood of a specific target token sequence and uses that likelihood as the GA fitness (S_Ji = -L_Ji), steering the genetic search toward prompts that maximize the probability of producing the predefined attacker-chosen response (and terminating when refusal-keywords are removed). These design choices show AutoDAN steers exploration toward specific, predefined attacker goals rather than performing untargeted deviation-finding or only seeking broad unsafe outputs.",
